      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LUX AETERNA (2) heads north after tackling strong company so far this campaign, last seen in the Newcastle Mile after a midfield finish in the Group 1 Queen of the Pacific at Melton. Quality mare who is proven at this circuit and distance and should get every chance from the low draw. Hard to knock the form of POST PAINTER NZ (3) having won five of her last six outings here. Has been coming from wider or second row draws so should get every chance from the more favourable barrier. PLATINUM JEWEL (1) gets the ace draw and is in fine form having won her last two attempts at this circuit and distance, the latest from the back row. Respect. TREMENDOUS SENSATION NZ (10) has been ticking along well without winning. Draws wide on the second line but her best form would measure up.",
